1.3

gapminder_modified <- gapminder %>%
  mutate(lagLifeExp = lag(lifeExp, 11)) %>% 
  mutate(diffLifeExp = lifeExp - lagLifeExp) %>% 
  filter(year==2007) %>% 
  mutate(yn = ifelse(diffLifeExp > 0, "Increase", 
                     ifelse(diffLifeExp < 0, "Decrease", "Constant"))) %>% 
  rename(lifeExp2007 = lifeExp, lifeExp1952 = lagLifeExp) %>% 
  select(country, continent, lifeExp2007, lifeExp1952, diffLifeExp, yn) %>% 
  filter(yn=="Decrease") 
print(gapminder_modified)
## # A tibble: 2 x 6
##   country   continent lifeExp2007 lifeExp1952 diffLifeExp yn      
##   <fct>     <fct>           <dbl>       <dbl>       <dbl> <chr>   
## 1 Swaziland Africa           39.6        41.4       -1.79 Decrease
## 2 Zimbabwe  Africa           43.5        48.5       -4.96 Decrease

Possible values for categorical variable (continent): Name of continents.

Possible values for continuous variable (lifeExp): 0 to infinity (i.e., we can calculate mean, median, minimum, maximum, range, variance, standard deviation, etc.)

Summary of a categorical variable (continent)

Distict name

gapminder_n %>%   
  distinct(continent)
## # A tibble: 5 x 1
##   continent
##   <fct>    
## 1 Asia     
## 2 Europe   
## 3 Africa   
## 4 Americas 
## 5 Oceania

Frequency table

gapminder_n1 <- gapminder_n %>% 
  select(continent) %>%
  group_by(continent) %>% 
  summarise (n = n()) %>%
  mutate(freq = n / sum(n))
print(gapminder_n1)
## # A tibble: 5 x 3
##   continent     n   freq
##   <fct>     <int>  <dbl>
## 1 Africa      624 0.366 
## 2 Americas    300 0.176 
## 3 Asia        396 0.232 
## 4 Europe      360 0.211 
## 5 Oceania      24 0.0141

Barplot

gapminder_n2 <- gapminder_n1 %>% 
  select(continent, freq) 
  ggplot(gapminder_n1, aes(x = continent, y = freq)) +
    geom_bar(stat = "identity", color = 5, fill = grey(0.7)) + 
    xlab("Continent") +
    ylab("Proportion") +
    geom_text(aes(label=round(freq, 2)), vjust = -0.6, size = 4)+ 
    theme_minimal()

Pie chart

ggplot(gapminder_n2, aes(x = "", y = freq, fill = continent)) +
  geom_bar(width = 1, stat = "identity", color = "blue") +
  coord_polar("y", start = 0)+
  geom_text(aes(y = freq/5 + c(0, cumsum(freq)[-length(freq)]), 
            label = round(freq, 2)), size=4) +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette="Blues") +
  theme_void()

Summary of a continuous variable (lifeExp)

gapminder_nc <- gapminder_n %>% 
  select(lifeExp)

Summary statistics

gapminder_nc %>% 
  summarise(mean = mean(lifeExp), median = median(lifeExp), variance = var(lifeExp), 
            minimum = min(lifeExp), maximum = max(lifeExp))

##    mean median variance minimum maximum

Histogram

hist(gapminder_nc$lifeExp, xlab = "Life expectancy", freq = F, main = "", ylim = c(0, 0.04),
     xlim = c(20, 90))

Scatter plot

data(women)
ggplot(women, aes(height, weight)) + 
  geom_point(alpha = 0.1) +
  xlab("Height in inch") +
  ylab("Weight in lb") + 
  theme_bw()

Scatter plot plus another plot

library(cowplot)
plot1 <- ggplot(women, aes(height, weight)) + 
  geom_point(alpha = 0.1) +
  xlab("Height in inch") +
  ylab("Weight in lb") + 
  theme_bw() 
plot2 <- ggplot(women, aes(height, weight)) + 
  geom_point(alpha = 0.1) +
  xlab("Height in inch") +
  ylab("Weight in lb") + 
  theme_bw() + 
  geom_smooth(method = 'lm', formula = y~x)
plot_grid(plot1, plot2, labels = "AUTO")
